    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="719"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d719">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/1141</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                    </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-28">
                        <hi rend="italic">October 28, 1914</hi>.</date>
                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 10 p.m.</hi>] </dateline>
                <p rend="center">[Telegram]</p>
                <p>Referring to my 926,<note n="1" xml:id="d719fn1">Not printed.</note> October 27.
                    A German mine field has been discovered off the north coast of Ireland and the
                    British Admiralty warns shipping not to pass within 60 miles of Tory Island. One
                    British ship bound from Manchester to Montreal struck a mine there and went
                    down. This mine field is in a location which suggests that it was meant rather
                    for merchant than naval ships.</p>
                <p>Part of channels of the Thames have been closed by Admiralty.</p>
                <p>A Dutch ship struck a mine 40 miles north of Ymuiden and sank.</p>
                <p>The sinking of the passenger boat across the Channel by a mine is disputed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PWH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
